            <fr:title text="Towards univalent reference types › models of iGDTT"><fr:link href="jms-00OI.xml" title="Towards univalent reference types" addr="jms-00OI" type="local"><fr:em><fr:link href="sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2024-univalent.xml" title="Towards univalent reference types" addr="sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2024-univalent" type="local">Towards <fr:strong>univalent</fr:strong> reference types</fr:link></fr:em></fr:link> › models of <fr:strong>iGDTT</fr:strong></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Slide</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p><fr:link href="palombi-sterling-2023.xml" title="Classifying topoi in synthetic guarded domain theory: the universal property of multi-clock guarded recursion" addr="palombi-sterling-2023" type="local">Palombi and S. (2023)</fr:link> have contributed a modular method for building models of (non-univalent) guarded dependent type theory over an arbitrary base topos. As applied by <fr:link href="sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2022.xml" title="Denotational semantics of general store and polymorphism" addr="sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2022" type="local">SGB’22</fr:link>:</fr:p>
            <fr:ol><fr:li>Any realisability topos <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {E}]]></fr:tex> contains an impredicative universe <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {M}_{\mathcal {E}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Pick any <fr:em>internal</fr:em> well-founded order <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {O}\in \mathbb {M}_{\mathcal {E}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Then the <fr:em>relative</fr:em> presheaf topos <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {F} :\equiv  {\mathopen {}\left  [\mathbb {O}^{\mathsf {op}},\mathcal {E}\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is a model of guarded recursion and contains an impredicative universe <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {M}_{\mathcal {F}}]]></fr:tex> defined from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {M}_{\mathcal {E}}]]></fr:tex> by <fr:link href="hofmann-streicher-1997.xml" title="Lifting Grothendieck universes" addr="hofmann-streicher-1997" type="local">Hofmann—Streicher lifting</fr:link>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
